# Spaghetti alla carbonara

## Ingredients (4 servings)
- 350 g spaghetti
- 200 g guanciale
- 3 egg yolks + 1 whole egg
- 100 g Pecorino Romano, grated
- Black pepper

## Instructions

🍝 Spaghetti alla Carbonara (Concise Version)


Cook the guanciale  
Dice and sauté until crispy. Keep the fat in the pan.

Prepare the sauce  
Whisk eggs, Pecorino, and black pepper into a thick cream.

Cook the pasta  
Boil spaghetti in salted water until al dente.

Combine  
Toss spaghetti with guanciale and its fat over medium heat for a few seconds.

Cream the sauce  
Remove from heat. Add the egg–cheese mixture and stir quickly, adding a little pasta water if needed for a silky texture.

Serve  
Plate and finish with more Pecorino and black pepper.

Notes
No cream, no garlic, no onion — traditional Roman style.

Heat control is essential to avoid scrambling the eggs.

